{"info": {"author": "Marquis Kurt", "author_email": "software@marquiskurt.net", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "# Ren'Py Distribution Tools\n\nA set of tools to make Ren'Py distribution less of a pain in the arse.\n\n[![MPL](https://img.shields.io/github/license/alicerunsonfedora/renpy-distribute-tools)](LICENSE.txt) \n![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.7+-blue.svg) \n\n## Installing `renpy-distribute-tools`\n\nTo install via PyPI:\n\n```\npip install renpy-distribute-tools\n```\n\nOr, if you're using a Poetry project, just add the dependency:\n\n```\npoetry add renpy-distribute-tools\n```\n\n## Building from source\n\nRen'Py Distribute Tools is a Poetry project and can be built using Poetry's `build` command.\n\n1. Clone the repository.\n2. In the root of the project, run `poetry install`.\n3. Finally, run `poetry build`.\n\n## What's included\n\nThe Ren'Py Distribution Tools set comes with utilities that make it easy to do the following:\n\n- Modifying a visual novel's `Info.plist`.\n- Code-signing the visual novel binaries in the Mac app with entitlements.\n- Creating a ZIP copy of the Mac app and sending it to Apple's notarization servers.\n- Stapling the notarization ticket to a macOS app.\n\n## Usage\n\nSee the [documentation](https://alicerunsonfedora.github.io/renpy-distribute-tools) for more info.", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/alicerunsonfeodra/renpy-distribute-tools", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "renpy-distribute-tools", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/renpy-distribute-tools/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/renpy-distribute-tools/", "project_urls": {"Documentation": "https://marquiskurt.net/renpy-distribute-tools/", "Homepage": "https://github.com/alicerunsonfeodra/renpy-distribute-tools"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/renpy-distribute-tools/0.3.1/", "requires_dist": ["pylint (>=2.4.4,<3.0.0)"], "requires_python": ">=3.7", "summary": "Utilities that make Ren'Py distribution less of a pain in the arse", "version": "0.3.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Ren'Py Distribution Tools</h1>\n<p>A set of tools to make Ren'Py distribution less of a pain in the arse.</p>\n<p><a href=\"LICENSE.txt\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"MPL\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/2eb10268b6cb2d2e0d7c03ed0012c1e6a4a42dc0/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f6769746875622f6c6963656e73652f616c69636572756e736f6e6665646f72612f72656e70792d646973747269627574652d746f6f6c73\"></a>\n<img alt=\"Python\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/d7ca45f98bb42530c497ea344d405f84abf0cb71/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f707974686f6e2d332e372b2d626c75652e737667\"></p>\n<h2>Installing <code>renpy-distribute-tools</code></h2>\n<p>To install via PyPI:</p>\n<pre><code>pip install renpy-distribute-tools\n</code></pre>\n<p>Or, if you're using a Poetry project, just add the dependency:</p>\n<pre><code>poetry add renpy-distribute-tools\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Building from source</h2>\n<p>Ren'Py Distribute Tools is a Poetry project and can be built using Poetry's <code>build</code> command.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Clone the repository.</li>\n<li>In the root of the project, run <code>poetry install</code>.</li>\n<li>Finally, run <code>poetry build</code>.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>What's included</h2>\n<p>The Ren'Py Distribution Tools set comes with utilities that make it easy to do the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Modifying a visual novel's <code>Info.plist</code>.</li>\n<li>Code-signing the visual novel binaries in the Mac app with entitlements.</li>\n<li>Creating a ZIP copy of the Mac app and sending it to Apple's notarization servers.</li>\n<li>Stapling the notarization ticket to a macOS app.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>See the <a href=\"https://alicerunsonfedora.github.io/renpy-distribute-tools\" rel=\"nofollow\">documentation</a> for more info.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7000250, "releases": {"0.3.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "49a6ab2a8a34d7def225eae5241a16f2", "sha256": "bc010d9860a5c658fbd4e0d29642da3bedf99144d57256edcc8e271a9e0f3cfb"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "renpy_distribute_tools-0.3.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "49a6ab2a8a34d7def225eae5241a16f2", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.7", "size": 6409, "upload_time": "2020-02-05T13:25:47", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-05T13:25:47.590445Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/03/d5/521953cf2ddce72e98e4428fbdd9ec5553fae553283e03e1683f01831f9b/renpy_distribute_tools-0.3.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "15b8834668ff0fd39e73cd4a9a6b2d78", "sha256": "4d5bfd27b5a95e975a43aace145b2c95e360e4975a0455fb50e56aceec60c2e2"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "renpy-distribute-tools-0.3.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "15b8834668ff0fd39e73cd4a9a6b2d78", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.7", "size": 5241, "upload_time": "2020-02-05T13:25:46", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-05T13:25:46.414483Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/84/d0/82ddfbe6d3d669bab151d07edee040c2e9517a52d73f8b03b0b840da8d9b/renpy-distribute-tools-0.3.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.3.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "03b5e31246399a8a7ea6e720661335bd", "sha256": "6a46f9291dfe5e480bb854437c702eb7951dca0db812821777cff5c6a7ab1bd7"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "renpy_distribute_tools-0.3.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": fal